# Releases: Always Attach the APK

For **every** GitHub release in this repo (production or ad-hoc), **attach the installable Android APK** as a release asset. Do not publish a release with only source or notes—users must be able to download and install from the release page.

## APK paths (this project)

Version is embedded in the filename (`year.month.day.minutesSinceMidnight`). After building from `android/`:

| Build        | Output file |
|-------------|-------------|
| Debug       | `android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/turnTable.debug-<version>.apk` |
| Release     | `android/app/build/outputs/apk/release/turnTable.release-<version>.apk` |

Run `./gradlew printAppVersion` to print `<version>` and `versionCode`. Use **release** (`assembleRelease`) for distribution; configure `keystore.properties` or env vars for store signing (otherwise Gradle warns and signs the release variant with the debug keystore).

## Checklist (before publishing any release)

1. `./gradlew assembleDebug` and/or `./gradlew assembleRelease` (from `android/`).
2. Confirm the APK exists at one of the paths above.
3. Create the tag/release and **upload the APK** (`gh release upload`, GitHub UI “Attach binaries”, or equivalent).
4. Optionally note the attached file name in release notes.

## Example (GitHub CLI)

```bash
cd android && ./gradlew assembleRelease
VER=$(./gradlew -q printAppVersion | cut -d' ' -f1)
gh release create "v${VER}" \
  "app/build/outputs/apk/release/turnTable.release-${VER}.apk" \
  --title "turnTable ${VER}" --notes-file CHANGELOG.md
```

**Never** ship a release without at least one APK asset for this Android app.
